name: HTMLObjectElement
description: The HTMLObjectElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those on the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <object> element, representing external resources.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.align
members.description: Is a DOMString representing an enumerated property indicating alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", "justify", and "center".

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.archive
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the archive HTML attribute, containing a list of archives for resources for this object.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.border
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the border HTML attribute, specifying the width of a border around the object.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.code
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the name of an applet class file, containing either the applet's subclass, or the path to get to the class, including the class file itself.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.codeBase
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the codebase HTML attribute, specifying the base path to use to resolve relative URIs.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.codeType
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the codetype HTML attribute, specifying the content type of the data.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.contentDocument
members.description: Returns a Document representing the active document of the object element's nested browsing context, if any; otherwise null.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.contentWindow
members.description: Returns a WindowProxy representing the window proxy of the object element's nested browsing context, if any; otherwise null.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.data
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the data HTML attribute, specifying the address of a resource's data.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.declare
members.description: Is a Boolean that reflects the declare HTML attribute, indicating that this is a declaration, not an instantiation, of the object.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.form
members.description: Retuns a HTMLFormElement representing the object element's form owner, or null if there isn't one.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.height
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the height HTML attribute, specifying the displayed height of the resource in CSS pixels.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.hspace
members.description: Is a long representing the horizontal space in pixels around the control.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.name
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the name HTML attribute, specifying the name of the browsing context.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.standby
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the standby HTML attribute, specifying a message to display while the object loads.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.tabindex
members.description: Is a long representing the position of the element in the tabbing navigation order for the current document.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.type
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the type HTML attribute, specifying the MIME type of the resource.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.typeMustMatch
members.description: Is a Boolean that reflects the typemustmatch HTML attribute, indicating if the resource specified by data must only be played if it matches the type attribute.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.useMap
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the usemap HTML attribute, specifying a <map> element to use.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.validationMessage
members.description: Returns a DOMString representing a localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.validity
members.description: Returns a ValidityState with the validity states that this element is in.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.vspace
members.description: Is a long representing the horizontal space in pixels around the control.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.width
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the width HTML attribute, specifying the displayed width of the resource in CSS pixels.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.willValidate
members.description: Returns a Boolean that indicates whether the element is a candidate for constraint validation. Always false for HTMLObjectElement objects.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.checkValidity()
members.description: Retuns a Boolean that always is true, because object objects are never candidates for constraint validation.

members.name: HTMLObjectElement.setCustomValidity()
members.description: Sets a custom validity message for the element. If this message is not the empty string, then the element is suffering from a custom validity error, and does not validate.
